# Conversation Summarization System

The conversation summarization system manages long AI conversations by automatically summarizing older parts when token limits are exceeded.

## Architecture Separation

**IMPORTANT**: The system separates two distinct concepts:

- **`RunRequest.History`** - Past conversations (text only, no files)
- **`RunRequest.Files`** - Current request media files (images, PDFs, etc.)

## Core Components

- **[ConversationSummarizer](mdc:engine/conversation_summary.go)** - Main summarization engine
- **[ConversationSummaryConfig](mdc:config/ai.go)** - Configuration for summarization behavior
- **Token Management** - Uses TokenCounter interface for accurate counting

## Key Methods

```go
// Count tokens in different contexts
func (cs *ConversationSummarizer) CountTokens(text string) int
func (cs *ConversationSummarizer) CountConversationTokens(conversations []Conversation) int
func (cs *ConversationSummarizer) CountRequestFilesTokens(files []File) int

// Main processing method
func (cs *ConversationSummarizer) ProcessConversationHistory(ctx context.Context, conversations []Conversation, requestFiles []File) (*ConversationHistoryResult, error)
```

## Configuration Options

- `MaxTokens` - Maximum tokens for conversation history
- `SummaryTokens` - Target tokens per summary
- `TokenProvider` - "auto", "openai", or "anthropic"
- `ModelForSummary` - LLM model for generating summaries

## Integration Pattern

The summarizer is integrated into the prompt building process in [prompt.go](mdc:engine/prompt.go):

```go
result, err := s.conversationSummarizer.ProcessConversationHistory(ctx, req.History, req.Files)
```
